{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/make/robot/5-servos.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>A new spin to my strange purchase of 5 servo drives. Why strange? Because 5 servos is not enough to make a spider (a hexapod robot).</p>\n<p>Here is a list of hexapods</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/NeoProg2013/AIWM_hexapod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Artificial intelligence walking machine</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>This time I want to create an arm. 5 servos should be enough for single arm robot.</p>\n<h2 id=\"main-beginner-questions\" style=\"position:relative;\">Main beginner questions<a href=\"#main-beginner-questions\" aria-label=\"main beginner questions permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>acrilic or plywood or ABS?</li>\n<li>in another words: laser cut or 3d print?</li>\n<li>joints. at least I know, that they should be rigid (<a href=\"https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2727176\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2727176</a>) not pulled be lines (<a href=\"https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3105948\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3105948</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"inspiration\" style=\"position:relative;\">Inspiration<a href=\"#inspiration\" aria-